data.description: Well maintained 2+ story brick colonial has retained it's original turn of the century feel by keeping it's hardwood floors, plaster walls, giant windows and five, yes five, converted to gas fireplaces. Growing family? Multi-generational living arrangements? Working from home? This house has enough room for everyone. There are five bedrooms, two full and one half bath. Closet space is amazing for house this age! Gorgeous hard wood floors throughout. Original casement trim has been painted bright white. Mostly newer windows. Slate roof has had recent work to replace any broken slates, dormers reflashed and chimney repointed. Fresh interior paint. Gas hot water boiler in basement has auxillary wood/coal burner. Huge basement is clean and plumbed for a third full bath.
